g.title: Legend Description
g.desc: Each riding has the area of seven hexagons. The equal areas r...
g.text: Each riding has the area of seven hexagons. The equal areas represent each riding's equal representation in the House of Commons. The colour of each riding shows the party declared the winner by both the CBC and CTV election desks as of 2021-10-07 08:00 AM EDT. Hover over each riding to see the riding name. In most cases, ridings that are next to each other geographically also have the same relatively positioning on the map. Thick black lines are provincial boundaries. Thin black lines are the approximate boundaries of metropolitan areas. Hover over each line to see the name of the border or metropolitan area.
